    SUPPORTING THE MISSION OF CIMM

    The Mission of the Channel Islands Maritime Museum is to preserve and share the wonders of our maritime heritage, highlight our complex interrelationships with the ecology of The Ocean, and showcase peoples creative expressions of everything related to the sea.

    CIMM is a renowned institution dedicated to preserving and interpreting maritime arts and culture. We offer a wide variety of exhibitions, programs, and educational opportunities for visitors of all ages.

    DONATE TO CIMM

    Help the Channel Islands Maritime Museum continue to grow and flourish. We are eternally grateful to all of our benefactors who contribute towards keeping us alive. All proceeds are directly reinvested into making the museum a better and more accessibleplace for you, yourfamily, and the community.

    DONATE TODAY

    MEMBERSHIP

    A museum membership is more than just a ticket to see art. It's an investment in your community, your future, and your children's future. When you buy a CIMM museum membership, you're supporting the museum's mission of education and outreach. You're helping to ensure that future generations will have the opportunity to experience the wonders of maritime art and culture. And you're making a statement that you believe in the importance of art and culture in our society.

    BECOME A MEMBER OR RENEW

    VOLUNTEER

    CIMM is proud of its tradition as a predominantly volunteer-run organization. Docents and volunteers have helped to staff the museum and its events for the last 32years and are truly the heart of the Museum.The Museum is always looking for friendly and eager volunteers. There are so many areas available to help support the Museum and its community of visitors.
